cs.GT, cs.DB, cs.DS, cs.BIO, cs.LG 

This paper is likely to belong to the cs.GT (Computational Geometry and Topology) sub-category as it deals with the analysis of genomic data and the identification of Single Nucleotide Polymorphisms (SNPs). It could also belong to the cs.DB (Databases) sub-category as it involves the storage and retrieval of genomic data. The cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category is also a possibility as the paper discusses multiplexing algorithms for SNP genotyping assays. The cs.BIO (Bioinformatics) sub-category is another likely possibility as the paper deals with the analysis of biological data. Finally, the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category is a possibility as the paper discusses the use of simulation results to evaluate the performance of the proposed genotyping assay architecture.
